final_hyps.green: The green object is the Goal that the agent must reach.
final_hyps.brown: Brown objects are False Walls. The agent can move through False Walls.
final_hyps.yellow: The yellow object is a Key. The agent can pick up the Key by moving into its space. While holding the Key, the agent is colored purple.
final_hyps.cyan: The cyan object is a KeyDoor. When the agent moves onto this object, the KeyDoor opens and the Key is destroyed. The agent cannot move through the KeyDoor while it is closed.

solve_plan: First, determine that the green object is the Goal object. Align the agent on the horizontal axis (y=10) by moving DOWN or UP. Because the agent is at y=8 and the goal is at y=10, it must move DOWN 2 times. Next, pick up the yellow Key by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is at x=5 and the yellow object is at x=13, it must move RIGHT 13 - 5 = 8 times. Then, move to reach the cyan KeyDoor (x=18) by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is now at x=13 and the cyan object is at x=18, it must move RIGHT 18 - 13 = 5 times. After picking up the yellow Key, the agent will be purple and can open the cyan KeyDoor. Finally, move to reach the goal (x=19) by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is now at x=18, it must move RIGHT 1 time.
